               <head>A collection of three works: two in Arabic on language and arithmetic, and a
                  third in Persian on geometry.</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary> This volume contains three works. The first one in Arabic, entitled
                        <title>Risālah al-Kāfī fī ʿIlmay al-ʿArūḍ wa-al-Qawāfī</title> (The Complete
                     Treatise on the Science of Metre and Rhyme), presents a brief Arabic treatise
                     the principles of metre and rhyme by <persName>Aḥmad ibn ʻAbbād Khawwāṣ (ca.
                        1378–1454)</persName>. The second Arabic text entitled <title>Khulaṣāt
                        al-Ḥisāb</title> (Summary of Accounting) by <persName>Bahāʾ al-Dīn ʻĀmilī
                        (1547–1621)</persName> relates concise work on mathematics and astronmy,
                     which is followed by Luṭf Allāh Muhandis' translation into Persian,
                        <title>Muntakhab Khulaṣāt al-Ḥisāb</title> (Selection of the Summary of
                     Accounting) which he completed at the behest of <persName role="pat">Mīr
                        Muḥammad Saʿīd bin Muḥammad Yaḥyā</persName>, in <date
                        calendar="Hijri-qamari" when="1681">1092 AH (1681 CE)</date> according to a
                     chronogram in the title.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_705-item1" n="1">
                     <author key="person_76203550" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/46986778">
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Khawwāṣ, Aḥmad ibn ʻAbbād,
                           ca. 1378–1454</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar">العبيدي، عبيد الله بن عبد الكافي</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_6590">Risālah al-Kāfī fī ʿIlmay
                        al-ʿArūḍ wa-al-Qawāfī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" key="work_6590">Risālah al-Kāfī fī
                        al-ʻArūḍ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_6590">رسالة الكافي في علمي العروض
                        والقوافي</title>
                     <incipit><locus from="1b" to="1b"> برگ ۱پ (folio 1b):</locus> الحمد لله على
                        الانعام والشكر له على الالهام والصلاة والسلام على خير الانام واله [اهله]
                        وصحبه السادة الاعلام وبعد فهذا تاليف الكافى فى علمى العروص والقوافى والله
                        الموفق وهو الهادي...</incipit>
                     <explicit><locus from="6b" to="6b"> برگ ۶پ (folio 6b):</locus> قال مولفه رحمة
                        الله تعال هذا اخر ما اوردنا حمعه ولله الحمد اولا واخرا سرا و علانیة. </explicit>
                     <colophon><locus from="6b" to="6b"> برگ ۶پ (folio 6b):</locus> وصلي الله علی
                        سیدنا محمد واله وصحبه وسلم تسلیماً کثیراً دایماً ابد ابد وام ملك الله نهایة
                        ماینبغي أن سیالة السائلون کلماً ذکره ذاکرون وغفله عن ذکره غافلون والحمد لله
                        رب العالمین. </colophon>
                     <colophon>Uninformative colophon.</colophon>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>A prior record mistakenly conflated this work with another by <persName
                           xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="standard" key="person_76203550"
                           ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/76203550/">ʻUbayd Allāh ibn ʻAbd al-Kāfī
                           ʻUbaydī, 14th cent.</persName>. For another copy of this work held in the
                        Rylands, completed on <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1853-05-03">24
                           Rajab 1269 AH (3 May 1853)</date> for <persName>Col. George William
                              Hamilton</persName>, see <ref target="manuscript_14145"><idno>Arabic MS 445</idno></ref> (Mingana cat. no.
                        432).</note>
                     <listBibl>
                        
                        <bibl> C. Brockelmann, <title level="m">Geschichte der Arabischen
                              Literatur</title> II (<pubPlace>Leiden</pubPlace>:
                              <publisher>Brill</publisher>, <date calendar="#Gregorian" from="1893"
